column5: Hey Guys,  I got a free pass to get away this weekend from Fri-Sun so I'm looking to take advantage.  My buddy are I are trying come up with a quick plan for a last minute trip.  Basically looking to rent a cottage or cabin at a good fishing lake within a couple hours from Barrie.  Preferably targeting walleye although really anything is good. We were kind of thinking Kawarthas although we don't know the lakes except Canal. Finding cottages open at this time of year is a bit difficult.  If anyone has any ideas you could share that'd be great.  It's just a little cold for camping.  Cheers Gov
I can probably get you on Temagami into a nice place that the power is still on... 3hr - 20 minute drive from Barrie. PM me if interested and I'll get you in touch with the "care taker".
We go here, http://www.pigeonlakeresort.com/, fairly regularly in the fall.  The cottages are basic but functional, cost is reasonable and you can launch/dock right into good water.  Dan
If it were me, I'd go with this offer.
You could try Big Moose Camp, Birch Hill Camp or Johnny's Camp on Lake Nosbonsing just outside of North Bay. Just google the names. Only be about 2.5 hrs door to door. Walleye, pike, bass and muskie.
Hook up with U & Me guide service, he has a cancellation....
